succor, so don't get them killed if you can avoid it. ***<br>
<br>
We're still trying to figure out a good pull strategy for Phinny that doesn't involved FD or an actual tank other than the pet.  We did manage one pull using a combination of multiple aggroing and coth.  Not bad considering a druid was puller.  There are &quot;theories&quot; that a lvl 60 can cause cancel magic from the top and phinny alone will come straight up.  I call it a theory because it does NOT work for us.  In fact, this method got the puller killed once and got the entire group, cept for 1 gater, killed the second time.<br>
<br>
As you can tell, I'm still hunting the perfect pulling system, however as for Phinny's power, I believe 100 percent that I could solo him or duo him with wifey's druid as healer.  If I ever get a 56 rezer to sit on the side-lines, I'm gonna try 3 different ideas I have for killing him and see.<br>
<br>
I am curious though...anyone know if, after mala, the swirlsping guardians (NOT the guardian seahorses) can be charmed.  I know they can not be mez'd or at least not easily. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udrizzinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drizzinn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 7:04:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=416.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.shadowsight.com/graphics/footman2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How many Mages for Phinny?</span><hr size=1> NOTE: This post contains theories including the &quot;lesser classes&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
