Now granted, I've been playing my Warrior quite a bit and my Mage has been sitting on the sidelines but, in my Exping experience, if you send a pet in where 3 or 4 mobs are, the pet will get all of them on him. In my theory, if you have say 6 Mages and all 6 chain cast pets (standard method of beginning the cast and typing /pet go away just before the summons is done), the 6 pets &quot;should&quot; keep aggro fairly well. The problem occurs when Phinny's low on health and everyone (Mages included if they still have mana) nukes Phinny at once. Now Phinny's dead but you have seahorses to contend with. Does a Druid/Wizard Root work on the seahorses?<br>
<br>
Theory 2: Each Druid and Wizard picks a seahorse. They all begin casting Root at the same time. As Roots land, pets go in on Phinny (pulling him close enough that the seahorses can't reach the pets?). Use the chain-pets method to bring him low, then everyone nukes him down. Loot Phinny and get the f*** outta there. This would probably include semi-chain casting the Roots. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231960" target="blank"><img src="http://www.shadowsight.com/graphics/cd5.jpg"></a><BR><B><i>Like the Lobster who eats lotsa butter.....SEIZE THE DAY ! ! !</i></b><BR>Carpe Diem - <a href="http://www.shadowsight.com/banesidhe">Bane Sidhe</a>Barbarian Warrior of 49 Papercuts<BR>
